The paper deals with the security of Deep Neural Networks (DNNs) and proposes a novel targeted bit Trojan attack. This suggests that the paper could belong to the cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves the use of DNNs and their weights, which could place it in the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category. The experiments are conducted on image datasets, indicating a possible fit in the cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) sub-category. The paper also involves the use of algorithms to generate triggers, which could place it in the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with the operation of the network, suggesting a possible fit in the cs.SY (Systems and Control) sub-category.
